ðŸ“˜ NumPy â€“ Lecture 1
(Excel â†’ Python Transformation)
ðŸ”¹ NumPy kya hota hai?

NumPy = Numerical Python
Ye Excel ke formulas, calculations aur fast processing ka Python version hai.



==============================================================================================================
| Salary |
| ------ |
| 25000  |
| 30000  |
| 28000  |
| 35000  |


import numpy as np

salary = np.array([25000, 30000, 28000, 35000])
print(salary)


| Excel Formula   | NumPy Code    |
| ----------------| --------------|
| =SUM(B2:B5)     | salary.sum()  |
| =AVERAGE(B2:B5) | salary.mean() |
| =MAX(B2:B5)     | salary.max()  |
| =MIN(B2:B5)     | salary.min()  |


================================================================================================================

=B2 + 5000

new_salary = salary + 5000
print(new_salary)

Condition â€“ IF Formula
-----------------------
Excel:
=IF(B2>28000,"Good","Low")
NumPy:
result = np.where(salary > 28000, "Good", "Low")
print(result)


high_salary = salary[salary > 28000]
print(high_salary)



